{"title_page": "Amir Tataloo", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Amir Tataloo\n| image            = Amir Tataloo 13960425001706636358215310283767 40691 (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Amirhossein Maghsoudloo\n| alias            = Tataloo\n| birth_date       = {{circa}} {{birth based on age as of date|32|2015|7|20}}<ref name=\"HK\">{{citation|author=Hanif Kashani|url =https://al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/07/FOR%2520WED%2520iran-rapper-tataloo-video.html|title=Iran\u2019s Foreign and Defense Policies|work=Al-Monitor|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/iran-blog/2015/jul/20/iran-military-goes-hip-hop-for-youth-appeal-amir-tataloo|title=How Iran is trying to win back the youth|work=Tehran Bureau|publisher=The Guardian|date=20 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| origin           = [[Iranian people|Iranian]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]] \n* [[Persian Rap|Rap]]<ref>{{citation|title=Youth, Space and Time: Agoras and Chronotopes in the Global City|publisher=BRILL|date=2016|page=227|author=Carles Feixa|author2=Carmen Leccardi|author3=Pam Nilan|isbn=9789004324589}}</ref>\n* [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"Z\">{{citation|title=Tataloo: the regular arrest of cursed celebrities in Iran|url=https://en.radiozamaneh.com/articles/tataloo-the-regular-arrest-of-cursed-celebrities-in-iran/|author=Rouzbeh Hamid|date=2 October 2016|access-date=11 June 2017|work=Radio Zamaneh}}</ref>\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n* Composer}}\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 2003\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Amirhossein Maghsoudloo''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062d\u0633\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u0642\u0635\u0648\u062f\u0644\u0648}}), better known by his [[stage name]] '''Amir Tataloo''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631 \u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648}}), is an Iranian [[singer-songwriter]].\n\n== Career ==\nAn [[underground musician]] unauthorized by the [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance]], Tataloo is \"a [[rapper]] with so many fans\" in words of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''<ref name=time/> and has a \"strong fan base\" among the youth in Iran according to [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]].<ref name=rfe/> His style has been described as \"popular flashy blend of pop, rap and R&B\".<ref name=\"HK\">{{citation|author=Hanif Kashani|url =https://al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/07/FOR%2520WED%2520iran-rapper-tataloo-video.html|title=Iran\u2019s Foreign and Defense Policies|work=Al-Monitor|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n== In politics ==\nTataloo formerly criticized the establishment for not licensing his music, which is deemed as \"Western, non-Iranian and immoral\" by the government,<ref name=time>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3958928/amir-tataloo-iranian-military/|title=This Is the Surprising Way the Iranian Military Responded to the Nuclear Deal|date=16 July 2015|publisher=Time|accessdate=31 July 2015|author=Kay Armin Serjoie}}</ref> although he kept distance from politics.<ref name=rfe>{{cite news|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/iran-rapper-detained-amir-tataloo-corruption-depravity/27946407.html|title=Iranian Fans Take To Social Media To Demand Rapper\u2019s Release|date=25 August 2016|publisher=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|accessdate=11 June 2017|author=Farangis Najibullah|author2=Mohammad Reza Yazdanpanah|last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he made a shift towards [[Iranian Principlists|Iran's conservative agenda]], pledging his support for the [[supreme leader of Iran]] and the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] on numerous occasions, as well as advocating mandatory ''[[hijab]]''.<ref name=\"HD\"/><ref name=\"F24\">{{cite web|url=http://observers.france24.com/en/20170501-rebellious-singer-forced-campaign-iran-religious-authorities|title=Has Iran's bad boy singer been forced to campaign for the religious authorities?|author=Ershad Alijani|date=5 January 2017|work=France24|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Tataloo initially endorsed [[Mohammad Bagher Ghalibaf]] for the [[Iranian presidential election, 2017|Iranian presidential election]]. Following Ghalibaf's drop-out, Tataloo sided with [[Ebrahim Raisi]] and publicly met him.<ref name=\"HD\">{{citation|author=Holly Dagres|authorlink=Holly Dagres|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2017/05/iran-raisi-tataloo-tatalee-election-race-endorsement-rapper.html|title=This young Iranian rapper may have cost Raisi the presidency|work=Al-Monitor|date=1 June 2017|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n=== Arrests ===\nTataloo was jailed three times in 2013, 2016 and 2020. Iranian morality police briefly arrested him in December 2013 for distributing his banned music to illegal foreign satellite channels.<ref name=\"Z\"/> He was arrested again on 23 August 2016 and spent two months in prison because of insulting the judge in the court hearing, however, he was reportedly charged with \u201cencouraging ''[[fasad]]'' and ''[[Islamic sexual jurisprudence#Prostitution|fahsha]]''\u201d.<ref name=\"Z\"/><ref name=\"HD\"/> His fans posted comments on social media accounts of the supreme leader of Iran, demanding his release.<ref name=rfe/>\n\nOn January 28, 2020, Tataloo was preparing to travel to the [[United Kingdom|UK]], where he was expected to play a concert in February. Tataloo who's real name is 'Amirhossein Maghsoudloo', was detained by [[Turkey|Turkish]] authorities in [[Istanbul]] after he was flagged as a [[wanted person]] by [[Interpol]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51287487|title=Iranian rapper detained by Turkish authorities|date=2020-01-28|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-28|language=en-GB}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arab.news/mcjex|title=Outspoken Iranian rapper Amir Tataloo arrested in Turkey|date=2020-01-28|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/iranian-rapper-arrested-in-turkey-tehran-authorities-say/30402470.html|title=Iranian Rapper Arrested In Turkey, Tehran Authorities Say|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> Turkish authorities stated that they have acted on an \"[[Interpol notice|Interpol red notice]]\" which was apparently issued by Iranian authorities - [[Law Enforcement Force of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iranian police]] have accused Tataloo of \"encouraging citizens, especially the youth, to use drugs\", according to a statement quoted by Iran's semi-official [[Iranian Students News Agency|ISNA news agency]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51287487|title=Iranian rapper detained by Turkish authorities|date=2020-01-28|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-28|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isna.ir/news/98110805973/\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631-\u0634\u062f|title=\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631 \u0634\u062f|date=2020-01-28|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0633\u0646\u0627|language=fa|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Nuclear Energy'' song ===\nDuring the Iran/5+1 nuclear talks in [[Vienna]], in July 2015, he released a song supporting the [[Iranian nuclear program]]. The music video was produced on the Iranian navy ship [[Iranian frigate Damavand|''Damavand'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2015/07/16/watch-iranian-rapper-celebrates-nuclear-power-from-the-deck-of-a-warship/|title=Watch: Iranian rapper celebrates nuclear power from the deck of a warship|author=Ishaan Tharoor|date=16 July 2015|work=Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n=== Telegram audio message ===\nHe published an audio message in May 2017 on his [[Telegram (messaging service)|Telegram]] channel, stating he \u201cknew nothing about politics\u201d and his political posts are forwarded by a friend in the [[Intelligence Organization of Army of the Guardians of the Islamic Revolution|IRGC Intelligence Organization]] with \u201cenough political information to provide us with excellent guidance\u201d.<ref name=\"HD\"/>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n* Zire Hamkaf (2011)\n* Tatality (2013)\n* Man (2014)\n* Number 6 (2015)\n* Mamnoue (2016)\n* Number 7 (2016)\n* Ghahreman (2017)\n* Amir (2018)\n* Sayeh (2019)\n* Jahanam (2019)\n* Barzakh (2020)\n* 78 (2020)\n\n== References==\n{{Commons category|Amir Tataloo}}\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tataloo, Amir}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Tehran]]\n[[Category:Iranian singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Iranian rappers]]\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani singers]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Amir Tataloo\n| image            = Amir Tataloo 13960425001706636358215310283767 40691 (cropped).jpg\n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Amirhossein Maghsoudloo\n| alias            = Tataloo\n| birth_date       = {{circa}} {{birth based on age as of date|32|2015|7|20}}<ref name=\"HK\">{{citation|author=Hanif Kashani|url =https://al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/07/FOR%2520WED%2520iran-rapper-tataloo-video.html|title=Iran\u2019s Foreign and Defense Policies|work=Al-Monitor|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/iran-blog/2015/jul/20/iran-military-goes-hip-hop-for-youth-appeal-amir-tataloo|title=How Iran is trying to win back the youth|work=Tehran Bureau|publisher=The Guardian|date=20 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]]\n| origin           = [[Iranian people|Iranian]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]] \n* [[Persian Rap|Rap]]<ref>{{citation|title=Youth, Space and Time: Agoras and Chronotopes in the Global City|publisher=BRILL|date=2016|page=227|author=Carles Feixa|author2=Carmen Leccardi|author3=Pam Nilan|isbn=9789004324589}}</ref>\n* [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"Z\">{{citation|title=Tataloo: the regular arrest of cursed celebrities in Iran|url=https://en.radiozamaneh.com/articles/tataloo-the-regular-arrest-of-cursed-celebrities-in-iran/|author=Rouzbeh Hamid|date=2 October 2016|access-date=11 June 2017|work=Radio Zamaneh}}</ref>\n}}\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n* Composer}}\n| instrument       = \n| years_active     = 2003\u2013present\n| label            = \n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = \n}}\n\n'''Amirhossein Maghsoudloo''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062d\u0633\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u0642\u0635\u0648\u062f\u0644\u0648}}), better known by his [[stage name]] '''Amir Tataloo''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631 \u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648}}), is an Iranian [[singer-songwriter]].\n\n== Career ==\nAn [[underground musician]] unauthorized by the [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance]], Tataloo is \"a [[rapper]] with so many fans\" in words of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''<ref name=time/> and has a \"strong fan base\" among the youth in Iran according to [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]].<ref name=rfe/> His style has been described as \"popular flashy blend of pop, rap and R&B\".<ref name=\"HK\">{{citation|author=Hanif Kashani|url =https://al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/07/FOR%2520WED%2520iran-rapper-tataloo-video.html|title=Iran\u2019s Foreign and Defense Policies|work=Al-Monitor|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n== In politics ==\nTataloo formerly criticized the establishment for not licensing his music, which is deemed as \"Western, non-Iranian and immoral\" by the government,<ref name=time>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3958928/amir-tataloo-iranian-military/|title=This Is the Surprising Way the Iranian Military Responded to the Nuclear Deal|date=16 July 2015|publisher=Time|accessdate=31 July 2015|author=Kay Armin Serjoie}}</ref> although he kept distance from politics.<ref name=rfe>{{cite news|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/iran-rapper-detained-amir-tataloo-corruption-depravity/27946407.html|title=Iranian Fans Take To Social Media To Demand Rapper\u2019s Release|date=25 August 2016|publisher=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|accessdate=11 June 2017|author=Farangis Najibullah|author2=Mohammad Reza Yazdanpanah|last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, he made a shift towards [[Iranian Principlists|Iran's conservative agenda]], pledging his support for the [[supreme leader of Iran]] and the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] on numerous occasions, as well as advocating mandatory ''[[hijab]]''.<ref name=\"HD\"/><ref name=\"F24\">{{cite web|url=http://observers.france24.com/en/20170501-rebellious-singer-forced-campaign-iran-religious-authorities|title=Has Iran's bad boy singer been forced to campaign for the religious authorities?|author=Ershad Alijani|date=5 January 2017|work=France24|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Tataloo initially endorsed [[Mohammad Bagher Ghalibaf]] for the [[Iranian presidential election, 2017|Iranian presidential election]]. Following Ghalibaf's drop-out, Tataloo sided with [[Ebrahim Raisi]] and publicly met him.<ref name=\"HD\">{{citation|author=Holly Dagres|authorlink=Holly Dagres|url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2017/05/iran-raisi-tataloo-tatalee-election-race-endorsement-rapper.html|title=This young Iranian rapper may have cost Raisi the presidency|work=Al-Monitor|date=1 June 2017|accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n=== Arrests ===\nTataloo was jailed three times in 2013, 2016 and 2020. Iranian morality police briefly arrested him in December 2013 for distributing his banned music to illegal foreign satellite channels.<ref name=\"Z\"/> He was arrested again on 23 August 2016 and spent two months in prison because of insulting the judge in the court hearing, however, he was reportedly charged with \u201cencouraging ''[[fasad]]'' and ''[[Islamic sexual jurisprudence#Prostitution|fahsha]]''\u201d.<ref name=\"Z\"/><ref name=\"HD\"/> His fans posted comments on social media accounts of the supreme leader of Iran, demanding his release.<ref name=rfe/>\n\nOn January 28, 2020, Tataloo was preparing to travel to the [[United Kingdom|UK]], where he was expected to play a concert in February. Tataloo who's real name is 'Amirhossein Maghsoudloo', was detained by [[Turkey|Turkish]] authorities in [[Istanbul]] after he was flagged as a [[wanted person]] by [[Interpol]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51287487|title=Iranian rapper detained by Turkish authorities|date=2020-01-28|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-28|language=en-GB}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://arab.news/mcjex|title=Outspoken Iranian rapper Amir Tataloo arrested in Turkey|date=2020-01-28|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/iranian-rapper-arrested-in-turkey-tehran-authorities-say/30402470.html|title=Iranian Rapper Arrested In Turkey, Tehran Authorities Say|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|language=en|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref> Turkish authorities stated that they have acted on an \"[[Interpol notice|Interpol red notice]]\" which was apparently issued by Iranian authorities - [[Law Enforcement Force of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Iranian police]] have accused Tataloo of \"encouraging citizens, especially the youth, to use drugs\", according to a statement quoted by Iran's semi-official [[Iranian Students News Agency|ISNA news agency]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51287487|title=Iranian rapper detained by Turkish authorities|date=2020-01-28|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-01-28|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.isna.ir/news/98110805973/\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631-\u0634\u062f|title=\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u0631\u062a\u062a\u0644\u0648 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631 \u0634\u062f|date=2020-01-28|website=\u0627\u06cc\u0633\u0646\u0627|language=fa|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Nuclear Energy'' song ===\nDuring the Iran/5+1 nuclear talks in [[Vienna]], in July 2015, he released a song supporting the [[Iranian nuclear program]]. The music video was produced on the Iranian navy ship [[Iranian frigate Damavand|''Damavand'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2015/07/16/watch-iranian-rapper-celebrates-nuclear-power-from-the-deck-of-a-warship/|title=Watch: Iranian rapper celebrates nuclear power from the deck of a warship|author=Ishaan Tharoor|date=16 July 2015|work=Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n=== Telegram audio message ===\nHe published an audio message in May 2017 on his [[Telegram (messaging service)|Telegram]] channel, stating he \u201cknew nothing about politics\u201d and his political posts are forwarded by a friend in the [[Intelligence Organization of Army of the Guardians of the Islamic Revolution|IRGC Intelligence Organization]] with \u201cenough political information to provide us with excellent guidance\u201d.<ref name=\"HD\"/>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n* Zire Hamkaf (2011)\n* Tatality (2013)\n* Man (2014)\n* Number 6 (2015)\n* Mamnoue (2016)\n* Number 7 (2016)\n* Ghahreman (2017)\n* Amir (2018)\n* Sayeh (2019)\n* Jahanam (2019)\n* Barzakh (2020)\n* 78 (2020)\n\nSingles\n\nFati 2019\n\n== References==\n{{Commons category|Amir Tataloo}}\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAU