{"title_page": "The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel", "text_new": "{{morerefs|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\n| image      = The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Side A of the US 12-inch single\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Grandmaster Flash]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 1981\n| format     = [[gramophone record|Vinyl]] / [[CD]] (1988)\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 7:12\n| label      = [[Sugar Hill Records (rap)|Sugar Hill Records]]\n| writer     = [[Clifton \"Jiggs\" Chase]], [[Melle Mel|Melvin Glover]], George Jackson, [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n| producer   = [[Sylvia Robinson]] and Joey Robinson, Jr.\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\"'''The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel'''\" is a single released by [[Grandmaster Flash]] in 1981. It is a live [[DJ mix]] recording of Flash scratching and mixing records from various groups using three turntables. This single was highly influential on many DJs, including rapper [[Dr. Dre]], and an early example of what would eventually be termed [[turntablism]].gay\n\n==Samples==\nAlong with spoken word vocals from a 1966 album titled ''The Official Adventures of Flash Gordon'', some of the primary records utilized to create the mix included: \n*[[Chic (band)|Chic]] \u2013 \"[[Good Times (Chic song)|Good Times]]\"\n*[[Blondie (band)|Blondie]] \u2013 \"[[Rapture (Blondie song)|Rapture]]\"\n*[[Queen (band)|Queen]] \u2013 \"[[Another One Bites the Dust]]\"\n*[[Sugarhill Gang]] \u2013 \"[[Eighth Wonder (song)|8th Wonder]]\"\n*[[The Furious Five]] \u2013 \"Birthday Party\"\n*[[Spoonie Gee]] \u2013 \"Monster Jam\"\n*[[Incredible Bongo Band|Michael Viner's Incredible Bongo Band]] \u2013 \"[[Apache (song)|Apache]]\"\n*[[Grandmaster Flash|Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five]] \u2013 \"Freedom\"\n*[[Sugarhill Gang]] \u2013 \"[[Rapper's Delight]]\"\n*[[The Hellers]] \u2013 \"Life Story\"\n\n==Track listing==\n\n===Vinyl===\n#\"The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\" - A-side\n#\"The Birthday Party\" (Instrumental) - B-side\n\n===CD===\n#\"The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\" .\n#\"[[The Message (Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five song)|The Message]]\"\n#\"It's Nasty (Genius of Love)\"\n\n==Reception==\nThe song was ranked at #2 among the top ten \"Tracks of the Year\" for 1981 by ''[[NME]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/bestalbumsandtracksoftheyear/1981-2-1045398 |title=Albums and Tracks of the Year |author= |date=2016 |publisher=[[NME]] |accessdate=2 November 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Chart positions==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Chart (1981)\n! Peak<br/>Position\n|-\n| U.S. ''Billboard'' [[R&B Singles]]\n|align=\"center\"| 55\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150217121914/http://www.grandmasterflashandthefuriousfive.com/ Group's Official Website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180612163606/https://www.thekiddcreole.com/ The Kidd Creole's Official Website]\n\n{{Grandmaster Flash}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel}}\n[[Category:1981 singles]]\n[[Category:1981 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sylvia Robinson]]\n[[Category:Sugar Hill Records (Hip-Hop label) singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Melle Mel]]\n\n\n{{1980s-single-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{morerefs|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\n| image      = The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Side A of the US 12-inch single\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Grandmaster Flash]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 1981\n| format     = [[gramophone record|Vinyl]] / [[CD]] (1988)\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 7:12\n| label      = [[Sugar Hill Records (rap)|Sugar Hill Records]]\n| writer     = [[Clifton \"Jiggs\" Chase]], [[Melle Mel|Melvin Glover]], George Jackson, [[Sylvia Robinson]]\n| producer   = [[Sylvia Robinson]] and Joey Robinson, Jr.\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\"'''The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel'''\" is a single released by [[Grandmaster Flash]] in 1981. It is a live [[DJ mix]] recording of Flash scratching and mixing records from various groups using three turntables. This single was highly influential on many DJs, including rapper [[Dr. Dre]], and an early example of what would eventually be termed [[turntablism]].\n\n==Samples==\nAlong with spoken word vocals from a 1966 album titled ''The Official Adventures of Flash Gordon'', some of the primary records utilized to create the mix included: \n*[[Chic (band)|Chic]] \u2013 \"[[Good Times (Chic song)|Good Times]]\"\n*[[Blondie (band)|Blondie]] \u2013 \"[[Rapture (Blondie song)|Rapture]]\"\n*[[Queen (band)|Queen]] \u2013 \"[[Another One Bites the Dust]]\"\n*[[Sugarhill Gang]] \u2013 \"[[Eighth Wonder (song)|8th Wonder]]\"\n*[[The Furious Five]] \u2013 \"Birthday Party\"\n*[[Spoonie Gee]] \u2013 \"Monster Jam\"\n*[[Incredible Bongo Band|Michael Viner's Incredible Bongo Band]] \u2013 \"[[Apache (song)|Apache]]\"\n*[[Grandmaster Flash|Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five]] \u2013 \"Freedom\"\n*[[Sugarhill Gang]] \u2013 \"[[Rapper's Delight]]\"\n*[[The Hellers]] \u2013 \"Life Story\"\n\n==Track listing==\n\n===Vinyl===\n#\"The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\" - A-side\n#\"The Birthday Party\" (Instrumental) - B-side\n\n===CD===\n#\"The Adventures of Grandmaster Flash on the Wheels of Steel\" .\n#\"[[The Message (Grandmaster Flash and the Furious Five song)|The Message]]\"\n#\"It's Nasty (Gen